item.text: [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin#The_block_chain Wikipedia definition]: The block chain is distributed; in order to independently verify the chain of ownership of any and every bitcoin (amount), each network node stores its own copy of the block chain.
A block chain is a transaction database shared by all nodes participating in a system.

A block chain is a transaction database shared by all nodes participating in a system. Block chain technology was popularised by cryptographic currency [[Bitcoin]]. Apart from financial transactions it as a number of applications. See [[Block Chain Projects]].
